headline_print_headline: Who Will Inherit the Throne at Vanity Fair?
byline_original: By Michael M. Grynbaum and Sydney Ember

abstract: If New York has turned inward and become obsessed with its screens, is Bill de Blasio, on his way to a second term, the mayor the city deserves?
snippet: If New York has turned inward and become obsessed with its screens, is Bill de Blasio, on his way to a second term, the mayor the city deserves?
lead_paragraph: It seemed perhaps all too appropriate that on the day after Bill de Blasio, master of somnolent arrogance, effectively won a second term as the mayor of New York City, came a report that a former product manager at Google and his partner had started a company called Bodega, meant to rid cities of actual bodegas.

abstract: NestlÃ©â€™s deal for a majority stake in Blue Bottle Coffee is in part an effort to reach coffee-loving millennials. Other food giants may be hunting similar targets.
snippet: NestlÃ©â€™s deal for a majority stake in Blue Bottle Coffee is in part an effort to reach coffee-loving millennials. Other food giants may be hunting similar targets.
lead_paragraph: NestlÃ© built its coffee kingdom on NescafÃ© and Nespresso pods. But the Swiss food giant is aiming higher with its newest deal: buying a majority stake in Blue Bottle Coffee, part of the vanguard of so-called third wave coffee. (Disclaimer: one of us drank a lot of Blue Bottle when living in San Francisco.)

headline_main: New York Today: Our Past in Pizza

abstract: The mayor may well coast to a second term in November, but just one day after a decisive primary victory, the governor needled him by praising his predecessor.
snippet: The mayor may well coast to a second term in November, but just one day after a decisive primary victory, the governor needled him by praising his predecessor.
lead_paragraph: It was the morning after a resounding primary victory for Mayor Bill de Blasio, the kind that political mandates are made of, and as luck would have it, the mayor of New York had a tailor-made moment to bask in the glow of electoral success.

abstract: The technology-focused graduate school, in a set of environmentally conscious buildings, is supposed to spur the development of the local tech sector.
snippet: The technology-focused graduate school, in a set of environmentally conscious buildings, is supposed to spur the development of the local tech sector.
lead_paragraph: Roosevelt Island, the skinny, two-mile-long strip of land between Manhattan and Queens in the East River, has been home to a prison, a lunatic asylum, a smallpox hospital and a workhouse, among other institutions.

abstract: From the early design stages, architects have integrated five immersive installations throughout the main academic building. Plop art it is not.
snippet: From the early design stages, architects have integrated five immersive installations throughout the main academic building. Plop art it is not.
lead_paragraph: Since the first crop of engineering graduate students arrived last month at the brand-new Cornell Tech campus on Roosevelt Island, many have been busy decoding the diagrams in Matthew Ritchieâ€™s dynamic mural rising four stories in the atrium of the Emma and Georgina Bloomberg Center, the main academic building.

abstract: The man who headed the C.D.C. under Obama will tackle new global health challenges, with $225 million from Gates, Bloomberg and Chan Zuckerberg
snippet: The man who headed the C.D.C. under Obama will tackle new global health challenges, with $225 million from Gates, Bloomberg and Chan Zuckerberg
lead_paragraph: After running the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention for eight years under President Obama, Dr. Thomas R. Frieden is starting a global health initiative that will focus on two big areas: heart health and epidemic preparedness.
